====================================================
MULTI-BRANCH BANKING MANAGEMENT SYSTEM (C++)
====================================================

STUDENT PROJECT DESCRIPTION:
This is a console-based Banking Management System developed in C++ using Object-Oriented Programming (OOP), file handling, and structured programming concepts. The system simulates real-world banking operations for multiple branches, customers, and bank tellers.

====================================================
HOW TO COMPILE AND RUN
====================================================

Option 1 (G++ Compiler - Recommended):
1. Open terminal or command prompt
2. Navigate to project folder
3. Compile using:

   g++ main.cpp -o bank

4. Run the program:

   ./bank   (Linux/Mac)
   bank.exe (Windows)

Option 2 (Online Compiler):
- Paste main.cpp into OnlineGDB or similar C++ compiler
- Click "Run"

====================================================
DEFAULT SYSTEM FLOW
====================================================

1. Start Program
2. Choose from Main Menu:
   - Create Account (Teller Function)
   - Customer Login
   - View Reports
   - Exit

====================================================
FEATURES IMPLEMENTED
====================================================

✔ Bank Teller Authentication (simulated)
✔ Customer Account Creation
✔ Auto-generated Account Numbers
✔ 5-digit PIN generation and encryption
✔ Customer Login with PIN verification
✔ Login attempt limiting (security feature)
✔ Deposit and Withdrawal transactions
✔ Balance inquiry
✔ Transaction logging system
✔ Multi-branch support structure
✔ Basic reporting system
✔ File handling using .dat files
✔ Object-Oriented Programming (Inheritance used)

====================================================
ACCOUNT TYPES (OOP INHERITANCE)
====================================================

The system supports multiple account types:

- Savings Account
- Cheque Account
- Fixed Deposit Account
- Student Account

(All derived from a base Account class)

====================================================
FILE STRUCTURE
====================================================

The system uses the following files:

- main.cpp              → Main program source code
- customers.dat         → Stores customer account data
- transactions.dat      → Stores transaction history
- system_config.txt     → System configuration (optional)
- README.txt            → Project documentation

====================================================
SECURITY FEATURES
====================================================

✔ PIN encryption using simple character shifting
✔ Maximum 3 login attempts before lockout
✔ Basic authentication system for customers
✔ Controlled access to account functions

====================================================
NOTES FOR DEMONSTRATION
====================================================

- PIN is shown only once during account creation
- Users must remember their account number and PIN
- All transactions update balance immediately
- Data is stored in files for persistence

====================================================
DEVELOPER NOTES
====================================================

This project was developed as an academic assignment to demonstrate:
- Object-Oriented Programming principles
- File handling in C++
- Real-world banking system simulation
- Structured programming and modular design

